records.nl_statement: Let $\mathcal{T}_\alpha$ be a family of topologies on $X$. Show that there is a unique smallest topology on $X$ containing all the collections $\mathcal{T}_\alpha$.

import Mathlib

open Filter Set TopologicalSpace

records.ground_truth:
def is_topology (X : Type*) (T : Set (Set X)) :=
  univ ∈ T ∧
  (∀ s t, s ∈ T → t ∈ T → s ∩ t ∈ T) ∧
  (∀s, (∀t ∈ s, t ∈ T) → sUnion s ∈ T)

  ∀ T'', is_topology X T'' → (∀ i, T i ⊆ T'') → T' ⊆ T'' :=

open Topology Filter Real Complex TopologicalSpace Finset
open scoped BigOperators

noncomputable def f : ℕ → ℝ
| 0 => sqrt 2

  : ∃ (x : ℝ), Tendsto f atTop (𝓝 x) ∧ ∀ n, f n < 2 :=

records.nl_statement: Prove that if $V$ is a complex inner-product space, then $\langle u, v\rangle=\frac{\|u+v\|^{2}-\|u-v\|^{2}+\|u+i v\|^{2} i-\|u-i v\|^{2} i}{4}$ for all $u, v \in V$.
records.lean_header:
import Mathlib

open InnerProductSpace ContinuousLinearMap Complex
open scoped BigOperators
records.ground_truth:
theorem exercise_6_7 {V : Type*} [NormedAddCommGroup V] [InnerProductSpace ℂ V] (u v : V) :
  ⟪u, v⟫_ℂ = (‖u + v‖^2 - ‖u - v‖^2 + I*‖u + I•v‖^2 - I*‖u-I•v‖^2) / 4 :=
records.baseline_candidate:
theorem autoformalized_theorem_2224 (V : Type*) [NormedAddCommGroup V] [InnerProductSpace ℂ V]
  [FiniteDimensional ℂ V] (u v : V) :
  inner u v = ((norm (u + v))^2 - (norm (u - v))^2 +
    (norm (u + Complex.I * v))^2 * Complex.I -
    (norm (u - Complex.I * v))^2 * Complex.I) / 4 := by sorry
